meta_description: Kenrich pumps are designed to pump most types of cementitious grouts (not recommended for chemical epoxy-type grouts). These pumps are ideal for grouting hollow metal door frames in place as well as placing grout anywhere that high pressure is not require
description: Kenrich pumps are designed to pump most types of cementitious grouts (not recommended for chemical epoxy-type grouts). These pumps are ideal for grouting hollow metal door frames in place as well as placing grout anywhere that high pressure is not required. Other applications include masonry restoration, fireproofing, soil stabilization, filling concrete block, installing NMB Splice Sleeves, waterproofing, tunnels, prison & jail construction, facility maintenance, parking structures, bridge repair, pumping cement slurries and general filling of voids.
short_description: Choice of hand-operated or air-powered models Easy to operate, minimal maintenance required Pumps most types of cementitious grouts Lightweight and portable; take pump to where you need the pump Makes an ideal tool for placing grout anywhere that high pressure is not required
